<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="un1013cb"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013cb"> (NLI.3) 13(cb)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Leadbeater saw 1,250,000 volts put into a man&apos;s body huge flames rushing from his palms, he lived.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">I have <mark>seen as much as a million and a quarter volts of electricity put into a human body, so that when the man held out his arm towards the wall huge flames rushed out from his fingers, yet he felt nothing unusual</mark>, nor was he in the least burnt unless he accidentally touched some external object; but even this enormous display of power had no effect whatever upon the serpent-fire. <small> <a name="THmay1910" href="/udra/udex.htm#THmay1910"><cite title="source">The Theosophist</cite></a> (May 1910), C.W. <mark>Leadbeater</mark>, &ldquo;FORCE-CENTRES AND THE SERPENT-FIRE&rdquo; p. 1085</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c07261c" href="../../../F/FF/fnbs/c07all.htm#c07261c">VI.C.07:261(c)</a> </dd> </dd></dl>
